element.text: the wishtree
Welcome to Wishtree.
I have been here before.
Enter

The tree's roots stretch into the sky, 
And gather the wishes left behind. 
Others may have come to visit. 
Be respectful, and please be kind.
Is this your first time here?
Yes, this is my first time.
No
Yes
Did you, or someone you know, lose a loved one due to COVID-19?
Dear ones and strangers alike are suffering, and the battle is not yet over.
Continue.
And lastly, make a silent wish for yourself. One day, it will transform you.
I made my wish.
Take a moment... to make a silent wish for one who may need it. Let it light their way.
Thanks for being here.

Desktop: WASD to move and mouse to turn.
VR: Press trigger button to fly in the direction you are facing.
This is a collective mind-space for reflection on the COVID-19 pandemic. It ponders on themes of loss, isolation, unity and bravery, with the tree as a locus of our wishes.
